<p class="indent1" style="-uslm-lc:I12" xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">The plan sponsor of a plan in critical status, as described in subsection <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002153">1</ref><note id="fn002153" type="footnote"><num>1</num> So in original. Probably should be “section”.</note> 432(b)(2), shall determine in writing the plan’s resource benefit level for each insolvency year, based on the plan sponsor’s reasonable projection of the plan’s available resources and the benefits payable under the plan.</p>
